article.description: Jonah Radebaugh had 19 points and 11 rebounds on Saturday and Northern Colorado beat North Dakota 79-66.
article.headline: Northern Colorado beats North Dakota 79-66
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jonah Radebaugh had 19 points and 11 rebounds on Saturday and Northern Colorado beat North Dakota 79-66. Radebaugh was 5 of 7 from 3-point range and 7 of 10 from the field overall. Jordan Davis and Andre Spight added 16 points each and Anthony Johnson scored 12 for the Bears (19-10, 10-6 Big Sky), who won their third straight and fifth of the last six. Northern Colorado led comfortably almost the entire way, opening to a 20-8 advantage and leading by as many as 19 in the first half. The Bears had their largest lead at 72-52 with five minutes left in the second half. Cortez Seales had 20 points, Conner Avants scored 19, Geno Crandall added 15 and Marlon Stewart 10 for North Dakota, which missed all eight of its 3-point attempts.
